{META_DATA}: HOW TO TRAIN YOUR DRAGON
{META_DATA}: Written by
{META_DATA}: Dean DeBlois & Chris Sanders
{META_DATA}: Final Draft February 13, 2010
{META_DATA}: FADE IN:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NORTH SEA/VILLAGE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We skim above a dark, wild ocean.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The camera turns toward a lone island, Berk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is a gigantic shard of rock jutting straight out of the water.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: This, is Berk.
{DIALOGUE}: It's twelve days North of hopeless, and a few degrees South of freezing to death.
{DIALOGUE}: It's located solidly on the meridian of misery.
{DIALOGUE}: The camera drifts over rolling hills to reveal a small village nestled on an outcropping of sea mounts.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: My village.
{DIALOGUE}: In a word, sturdy.
{DIALOGUE}: And it's been here for seven generations, but every single building is new.
{DIALOGUE}: The camera drifts closer, circling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: We have fishing, hunting, and a charming view of the sunsets.
{DIALOGUE}: The only problems are the pests.
{DIALOGUE}: You see, most places have mice or mosquitos.
{DIALOGUE}: We have... Sheep graze peacefully on a hillside.
{DIALOGUE}: Suddenly one is snatched.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. STOICK'S HOUSE - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A door is pulled open... as a DRAGON swoops directly toward it, BLASTING FIRE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door is SLAMMED.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fire shoots through the slats of wood, illuminating HICCUP, a gangly teenage Viking.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: ...dragons.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STOICK'S HOUSE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reopens the sizzling door, as leaps off of the front porch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He weaves through the erupting mayhem as Vikings pour out of the buildings, ready for a fight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 2.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: More dragons swarm in, setting rooftops alight and hauling off sheep.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Most people would leave.
{DIALOGUE}: Not us.
{DIALOGUE}: We're Vikings.
{DIALOGUE}: We have stubbornness issues.
{DIALOGUE}: Vikings sound the alarm.
{DIALOGUE}: Viking men and women pour out into the streets, axes in hand.
{DIALOGUE}: ON HICCUP darting through alleys, staying under eaves, making his way through the battle.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: My name's Hiccup.
{DIALOGUE}: Great name, I know.
{DIALOGUE}: But it's not the worst.
{DIALOGUE}: Parents believe a hideous name will frighten off gnomes and trolls.
{DIALOGUE}: Like our charming Viking demeanor wouldn't do that.
{DIALOGUE}: Dragons sweep back and forth, dodging axes and blasting the Vikings who throw them.
{DIALOGUE}: A burly warrior gets tossed in an explosion, knocking Hiccup to the ground.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VIKING
{META_DATA}: (FIERCE)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arggghhhhh!
{META_DATA}: (cheery, insane)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mornin'!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup gets to his feet and continues to rush past gigantic men and women.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Meet the neighbors.
{DIALOGUE}: Hoark the Haggard...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HOARK
{DIALOGUE}: What are you doing out!?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: ... Burnthair the Broad...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BURNTHAIR
{DIALOGUE}: Get inside!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: ... Phlegma the Fierce...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PHLEGMA THE FIERCE Get back inside!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 3.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: Ack.
{DIALOGUE}: He passes a silent ox of a viking, picking his ear.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Yep, just Ack.
{DIALOGUE}: Enter STOICK, the biggest Viking of all.
{DIALOGUE}: He yanks Hiccup from the path of a strafing dragon and holds aloft to the crowd.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup!?
{META_DATA}: (accusingly; to the crowd)
{DIALOGUE}: What is he doing out again?!
{META_DATA}: (TO HICCUP)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: What are you doing out?!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Get inside!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The flames light up his scowling face and matted red beard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sets Hiccup down and turns to the sky, searching.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (IN AWE)
{DIALOGUE}: That's Stoick the Vast.
{DIALOGUE}: Chief of the tribe.
{DIALOGUE}: They say that when he was a baby he popped a dragon's head clean off of its shoulders.
{DIALOGUE}: Do I believe it?
{DIALOGUE}: Stoick grabs a wooden cart and hurls it, knocking the strafing dragon out of the sky.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Yes I do.
{DIALOGUE}: An EXPLOSION forces Vikings to DUCK.
{DIALOGUE}: Stoick stands firm, brushing flaming debris off of his shoulder.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{META_DATA}: (barking; to his men)
{DIALOGUE}: What have we got?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VIKING #1
{DIALOGUE}: Gronkles.
{DIALOGUE}: Nadders.
{DIALOGUE}: Zipplebacks.
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, and Hoark saw a Monstrous Nightmare.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{DIALOGUE}: Any Night Furies?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VIKING #1
{DIALOGUE}: None so far.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 4.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{META_DATA}: (RELIEVED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Good.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VIKING
{DIALOGUE}: Hoist the torches!
{DIALOGUE}: Massive flaming braziers are raised on poles, lighting up the night sky... and revealing swirling dragons of all types.
{DIALOGUE}: Below, Hiccup crosses an open plaza and ducks into an open building with a tall chimney.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BLACKSMITH STALL - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He crosses behind a counter, where a peg-legged, one-armed hulk of a Blacksmith reshapes blades with a hammer and tongs appendage.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{DIALOGUE}: Ah!
{DIALOGUE}: Nice of you to join the party.
{DIALOGUE}: I thought you'd been carried off.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup dons a leather apron and starts to put away Gobber's scattered appendages.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: Who me?
{DIALOGUE}: Nah, come on!
{DIALOGUE}: I'm way too muscular for their taste.
{DIALOGUE}: They wouldn't know what to do with all this.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup strikes a bodybuilder pose.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{DIALOGUE}: They need toothpicks, don't they?
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup gets to work, transferring bent and chipped weapons to the forge as Vikings crowd the counter for replacements.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: The meathead with attitude and interchangeable hands is Gobber.
{DIALOGUE}: I've been his apprentice ever since I was little.
{DIALOGUE}: Well...littler.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON STOICK
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{DIALOGUE}: We move to the lower defenses.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll counter-attack with the catapults.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 5.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Armed men rush past, flanking others who carry sheep to safety.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stoick follows up the rear as, overhead, a dragon strafes the rooftops with Napalm-like fire.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: See?
{DIALOGUE}: Old village.
{DIALOGUE}: Lots and lots of new houses.
{META_DATA}: VIKING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FIRE!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In response, the fire brigade charges through the plaza -- four TEENS, tugging a large wooden cask on wheels.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: From it, they fill buckets of water to douse the flames.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One among them is a cute, energetic Viking girl.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup leans out of the stall to watch her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh and that's Fishlegs, Snotlout.
{DIALOGUE}: The twins Ruffnut and Tuffnut.
{DIALOGUE}: And...
{META_DATA}: (DREAMY)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Astrid.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SLOW-MOTION explosion erupts behind her, framing her in a sexy ball of fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The others join her, looking awesome and heroic.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Their job is so much cooler.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup tries to join them as they pass, but he's hooked by Gobber and hoisted back inside.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (PLEADING)
{DIALOGUE}: Ah, come on.
{DIALOGUE}: Let me out, please.
{DIALOGUE}: I need to make my mark.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, you've made plenty of marks.
{DIALOGUE}: All in the wrong places.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: Please, two minutes.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll kill a dragon.
{DIALOGUE}: My life will get infinitely better.
{DIALOGUE}: I might even get a date.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{DIALOGUE}: You can't lift a hammer.
{DIALOGUE}: You can't swing an axe... Gobber grabs a bola (iron balls connected by rope).
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 6.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ... you can't even throw one of these.
{DIALOGUE}: A Viking runs by and nabs it out of Gobber's hand, hurling it at a dive-bombing Gronkle.
{DIALOGUE}: The bola binds its legs, sending it into a heavy crash.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{META_DATA}: (ready with the answer)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay fine, but... He rushes to the back corner of the stall and presents a bizarre, wheel barrow-like contraption.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ... this will throw it for me.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup OPENS the hinged lid of the device.
{DIALOGUE}: An arm springs up, equipped with twin bows.
{DIALOGUE}: They prematurely launch a bola, narrowly missing Gobber... and taking out a Viking at the counter.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VIKING
{DIALOGUE}: Arggh!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{DIALOGUE}: See, now this right here is what I'm talking about.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: Mild calibration issue.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup.
{DIALOGUE}: If you ever want to get out there to fight dragons, you need to stop all... Gobber gestures in Hiccup's general direction.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ... this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{META_DATA}: (ASTONISHED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But... you just pointed to all of me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{DIALOGUE}: Yes!
{DIALOGUE}: That's it!
{DIALOGUE}: Stop being all of you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 7.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{META_DATA}: (THREATENING)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ohhhh...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{META_DATA}: (MIMICKING)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ohhhhh, yes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: You, sir, are playing a dangerous game.
{DIALOGUE}: Keeping this much, raw...Vikingness contained.
{META_DATA}: (BEAT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There will be consequences!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gobber tosses him a sword.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{DIALOGUE}: I'll take my chances.
{DIALOGUE}: Sword.
{DIALOGUE}: Sharpen.
{DIALOGUE}: Now.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup takes it begrudgingly and lobs it onto the grinding wheel.
{DIALOGUE}: He stews... fantasizing...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: One day I'll get out there.
{DIALOGUE}: Because killing a dragon is everything around here.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - LOWER PLAINS - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nadders land, gathering like seagulls around a seemingly vacant house.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: A Nadder head is sure to get me at least noticed.
{DIALOGUE}: The Nadders clamber onto the building, tearing the roof and walls apart.
{DIALOGUE}: Sheep pour out and SCATTER.
{DIALOGUE}: Elsewhere, hippo-like Gronckles pick drying racks clean of fish and fly off like loaded pelicans.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Gronckles are tough.
{DIALOGUE}: Taking down one of those would definitely get me a girlfriend.
{DIALOGUE}: A stealthy, snake-like dragon head peeks over a rooftop, breathing gas into a chimney.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 8.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: A Zippelback?
{DIALOGUE}: Exotic, exciting.
{DIALOGUE}: Two heads, twice the status.
{DIALOGUE}: A second head pokes through the door and lights it.
{DIALOGUE}: KABLAM!
{DIALOGUE}: The two heads fly through the explosion, their necks zipping together to reveal a single body.
{DIALOGUE}: It flies past Stoick as he climbs to the top of a CATAPULT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TOWER.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATAPULT OPERATOR
{DIALOGUE}: They found the sheep!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{META_DATA}: (FRUSTRATED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Concentrate fire over the lower bank!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CATAPULT OPERATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Fire!
{DIALOGUE}: Boulders are catapulted at the corralling Nadders... Just as a huge red dragon whips past, spraying the base of the catapult with sticky fire.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: And then there's the Monstrous Nightmare.
{DIALOGUE}: Only the best Vikings go after those.
{DIALOGUE}: They have this nasty habit of setting themselves on fire.
{DIALOGUE}: It emerges from the flames, climbing the catapult with a leering, toothy grin.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{DIALOGUE}: Reload!
{DIALOGUE}: I'll take care of this.
{DIALOGUE}: Stoick takes on the Nightmare, face to hammer.
{DIALOGUE}: Suddenly, a LOUD BALLISTIC MOANING streaks overhead.
{DIALOGUE}: The catapult crew ducks.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BLACKSMITH STALL - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON HICCUP, looking up from his work, reacting to the same sound.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: But the ultimate prize is the dragon no one has ever seen.
{DIALOGUE}: We call it the--
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 9.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VIKING
{DIALOGUE}: Night Fury!
{DIALOGUE}: Get down!
{DIALOGUE}: Vikings everywhere take shelter.
{DIALOGUE}: The moaning sound BUILDS.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - CATAPULT - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Monstrous Nightmare suddenly stops fighting and takes flight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stoick looks skyward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: STOICK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JUMP!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: KABOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Catapult EXPLODES as though hit by an artillery shell... sending Stoick and the crew leaping for their lives.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: This thing never steals food, never shows itself, and... The sound recedes, leaving the crippled catapult in flames.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.) (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ...never misses.
{META_DATA}: (BEAT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No one has ever killed a Night Fury.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: That's why I'm going to be the first.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE STALL Gobber trades his hammer for an axe.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{DIALOGUE}: Man the fort, Hiccup, they need me out there!
{DIALOGUE}: Gobber pauses.
{DIALOGUE}: Turns with a threatening glare.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Stay.
{DIALOGUE}: Put.
{DIALOGUE}: There.
{DIALOGUE}: You know what I mean.
{DIALOGUE}: Gobber charges into the fray, HOLLERING.
{DIALOGUE}: ON HICCUP, a smirk crosses his face.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - MOMENTS LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WHAM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup pushes his wheeled contraption through a wall of clustered Vikings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He weaves through the ongoing mayhem, as fast as his legs can carry him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 10.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VIKING #6 (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup, where are you going!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VIKING #7
{DIALOGUE}: Come back here!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: I know.
{DIALOGUE}: Be right back!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON THE PLAIN BELOW The Nadders have cornered the house-full of sheep.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They close in, ready to spring upon them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stoick suddenly appears, HURLING FISHING NETS over them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The surprised Nadders are caught.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stoick and his men rush in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A Nadder blasts a hole through its net.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stoick leaps onto it, clamping his thick arms around its head, forcing its jaws shut.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{DIALOGUE}: Mind yourselves!
{DIALOGUE}: The devils still have some juice in them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON THE PLAIN ABOVE Hiccup reaches a cliff overlooking the smoking CATAPULT and drops the handles to the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He cranks several levers, unfolding and then cocking the bowed arms of his contraption.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drops a bola onto a chamber and then pivots the weapon on a gimbal head toward the dark sky.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He listens, with his eye pressed to the scope, hand poised on the trigger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hears the NIGHT FURY approaching... and turns his aim to the defense tower.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It closes in for the final strike, completely camouflaged in the night.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{META_DATA}: (TO HIMSELF)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Come on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Give me something to shoot at, give me something to shoot at.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: KABLAM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tower topples.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The blast of fire illuminates the dragon for a split second.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup pulls the trigger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: KERTHUNK!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The flexed arms SNAP forward, springing the weapon off the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bola disappears into the sky, followed by a WHACK and a SCREECH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 11.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (surprised, then elated)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh I hit it!
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, I hit it!
{DIALOGUE}: Did anybody see that?
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup's victory is short-lived.
{DIALOGUE}: A Monstrous Nightmare appears, slithering up over the lip of the cliff.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Except for you.
{DIALOGUE}: ON STOICK, holding down the netted Nadders.
{DIALOGUE}: He hears a familiar HOLLER and looks up to see... HICCUP running through the PLAZA, SCREAMING, with the NIGHTMARE fast on his heels.
{DIALOGUE}: Alarmed, Stoick abandons the Nadders and runs off.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{META_DATA}: (to his men, re: the
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NADDERS)
{DIALOGUE}: DO NOT let them escape!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE PLAZA Vikings scatter as Hiccup dodges a near fatal blast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Nightmare's sticky, Napalm-like fire splashes up onto buildings, setting them alight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup ducks behind the last standing brazier -- the only shelter available.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Nightmare blasts it, spraying fire all around him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup peers around the smoldering post.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No sign of the Nightmare.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns back to find it leering at him, blocking his escape.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It takes a deep breath.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup is finished.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly, Stoick LEAPS between them, tackling the Nightmare to the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They tumble and wrestle, resuming their earlier fight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Nightmare tries to toast him, but only coughs up smoke.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: You're all out.
{DIALOGUE}: He smashes the Nightmare repeatedly in the face, driving it away.
{DIALOGUE}: It takes to the air and disappears.
{DIALOGUE}: Winded, Stoick turns to Hiccup.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, and there's one more thing you need to know...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 12.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The burnt brazier pole collapses, sending the massive iron basket crashing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It bounces down the hill, destroying as it goes and scattering the Vikings who were holding down the netted Nadders.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The freed dragons escape... with several sheep in tow.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry, dad.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - UPPER PLAZA - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The escaped Nadders fly past with sheep in their clutches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The raid is over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dragons have clearly won.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The murmuring crowd eyes Stoick, awaiting his response.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{META_DATA}: (SHEEPISH)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Okay, but I hit a Night Fury.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stoick grabs Hiccup by the back scruff of his collar and hauls him away, fuming with embarrassment.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: It's not like the last few times, Dad.
{DIALOGUE}: I mean I really actually hit it.
{DIALOGUE}: You guys were busy and I had a very clear shot.
{DIALOGUE}: It went down, just off Raven Point.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's get a search party out there, before it--
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{DIALOGUE}: --STOP!
{DIALOGUE}: Just....stop.
{DIALOGUE}: He releases Hiccup.
{DIALOGUE}: Everyone goes silent, staring expectantly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Every time you step outside, disaster follows.
{DIALOGUE}: Can you not see that I have bigger problems?
{DIALOGUE}: Winter's almost here and I have an entire village to feed!
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup looks around.
{DIALOGUE}: All eyes are upon him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: Between you and me, the village could do with a little less feeding, don't ya think?
{DIALOGUE}: A few rotund Vikings stir self-consciously.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 13.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{DIALOGUE}: This isn't a joke, Hiccup!
{META_DATA}: (EXASPERATED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Why can't you follow the simplest orders?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: I can't stop myself.
{DIALOGUE}: I see a dragon and I have to just... kill it, you know?
{DIALOGUE}: It's who I am, Dad.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{DIALOGUE}: You are many things, Hiccup.
{DIALOGUE}: But a dragon killer is not one of them.
{DIALOGUE}: Sting.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup looks around to see many nods of agreement.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Get back to the house.
{META_DATA}: (TO GOBBER)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Make sure he gets there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: I have his mess to clean up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stoick lumbers off in the opposite direction.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gobber leads Hiccup through the walk of shame.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They pass the teen fire brigade as they snicker.
