{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup tries to look away, but he's drawn back to its unnerving, unflinching stare.
{DIALOGUE}: With the dragon safety tangled in the ropes, Hiccup jabs with his dagger, puffing himself up with false bravado.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 19.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going to kill you, Dragon.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm gonna cut out your heart and take it to my father.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm a Viking.
{META_DATA}: (BEAT)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: I am a VIKING!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup raises the dagger, determined to prove his Viking- ness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dragon's labored breathing breaks Hiccup's clenched concentration.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He opens an eye, uncertainty leaking through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dragon holds the stare.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Something profound is exchanged.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally, the Night Fury closes its eye and lowers its head, resigned to its fate.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup tries to go through with it, holding the dagger aloft... fighting himself... until finally lowering it with a frustrated sigh.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks over the dragon's chaffed rope wounds.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (muttered, ashamed)
{DIALOGUE}: I did this.
{DIALOGUE}: He turns to leave.
{DIALOGUE}: Pauses.
{DIALOGUE}: And glances back at the dragon, chest heaving.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup GRUMBLES.
{DIALOGUE}: He checks over his shoulder to ensure that no one is watching... then hurries back to cut the ropes.
{DIALOGUE}: The Night Fury's eye shoots open.
{DIALOGUE}: With the dragon watching his every move, Hiccup hurriedly saws through the bola ropes.
{DIALOGUE}: As the last rope falls free, the Night Fury suddenly POUNCES!
{DIALOGUE}: In a blur, the dragon is upon him, pinning Hiccup down, grazing his neck.
{DIALOGUE}: Looking like it's about to kill him.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup is paralyzed.
{DIALOGUE}: The dragon's breath ruffles his hair.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup opens his eyes to find the Night Fury's wolf-like stare boring into him.
{DIALOGUE}: The exchange is intense, profound.
{DIALOGUE}: The dragon draws a deep breath, as though it's about to torch him, then lets out an ear-piercing scream instead.
{DIALOGUE}: It turns and takes flight, flapping violently through the canopy of trees.
{DIALOGUE}: It bashes against a nearby mountain side, recovers, and drops out of view some distance away.
{DIALOGUE}: Winded, Hiccup struggles to his feet, staggers a few steps, collapses to his knees, and faints.
