{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup looks overhead to see a steaming pit in the solid stone wall.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WOODS/HIDDEN COVE - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HICCUP, battered after another disastrous day in the ring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He studies the remnants of the discarded bola... revealing that he's back at the scene of the crime.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 28.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{META_DATA}: (MUTTERED)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: So...why didn't you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drops the bola and presses on in the direction it flew off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drops into a rocky crevice and follows it to an... ISOLATED COVE complete with a pristine spring pool.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He scans the high stone walls... then notices a single black SCALE on the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He crouches and picks it up, studying it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Well this was stupid.
{DIALOGUE}: SUDDENLY, the NIGHT FURY blasts past him.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup recoils, watching the massive beast struggle to climb the walls.
{DIALOGUE}: It flaps violently, then peels away to a rough landing.
{DIALOGUE}: The dragon is trapped.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup grins, excited to see it again, and slips closer.
{DIALOGUE}: He watches as the dragon, exhausted and frustrated, leaps into the air, beating its wings furiously.
{DIALOGUE}: Again and again, it rolls uncontrolled and CRASHES heavily.
{DIALOGUE}: As if remembering to snap a photo, Hiccup pulls a leather- bound book and flips past drawings of weapons to a blank page.
{DIALOGUE}: He sketches the dragon quickly, desperate to record the image.
{DIALOGUE}: The Fury claws at the steep rock walls, trying climb out of the cove.
{DIALOGUE}: It SLIPS and falls hard, crushing several saplings.
{DIALOGUE}: The Fury rolls back to his feet and slowly crawls to the water's edge.
{DIALOGUE}: He spots fish in the shallow water and snaps at them... but comes up empty.
{DIALOGUE}: He lowers his head, looking weakened.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (MUTTERED)
{DIALOGUE}: Why don't you just...fly away?
