{DIALOGUE}: Inscribed upon it are several tail positions and their pedal position equivalents.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Here we go.
{DIALOGUE}: Here we go...position three, no four.
{DIALOGUE}: He presses the pedal, causing the tail to flare.
{DIALOGUE}: They roll off into an arcing bank, gloriously lit by the late afternoon sun.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup tucks tight against his neck, thrilled that his new harness and vest are holding.
{DIALOGUE}: The foot controls make the tail appendage quick and responsive.
{DIALOGUE}: He watches Toothless' every fluctuation, trying to match it with the prosthetic.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup sizes up a target -- a towering arch of stone, rising from the sea.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 53.
