{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stoick leans close to Toothless, meeting him eye to eye.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (PRIVATELY)
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you... for saving my son.
{DIALOGUE}: Gobber looks Hiccup up and down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GOBBER
{DIALOGUE}: Well, you know... most of him.
{DIALOGUE}: Stoick glances back at him.
{DIALOGUE}: Gobber shrugs, redirecting his eyes toward...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 101.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. STOICK'S HOUSE - DAY
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CLOSE ON
{DIALOGUE}: HICCUP, asleep, his head on a pillow.
{DIALOGUE}: Healing scars on his face show that maybe a week or two have passed.
{DIALOGUE}: Toothless hovers over him, WHINING and GRUMBLING impatiently.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup stirs.
{DIALOGUE}: Opens his eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{META_DATA}: (GROGGY)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Oh, hey Toothless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toothless excitedly nuzzles and nudges Hiccup.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, okay!
{DIALOGUE}: I'm happy to see you too, bud.
{DIALOGUE}: Now just-- Toothless steps on his groin, causing Hiccup to sit BOLT UPRIGHT with a YELP.
{DIALOGUE}: He looks around, confounded.
{DIALOGUE}: He's in his bed, moved beside the fire pit on the main floor of his house.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm in my house.
{META_DATA}: (re: Toothless, leaning over him, excited)
{DIALOGUE}: You're in my house.
{DIALOGUE}: Toothless TEARS around the room, knocking things over, far too big for the space.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Uh...does my dad know you're in here?!
{DIALOGUE}: Toothless pauses at the foot of the bed, tongue wagging.
{DIALOGUE}: He eyes the rafters... and LEAPS UP onto them, brimming with 'happy dog' energy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (DISTRESSED)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, okay -- no Toothless!
{DIALOGUE}: Aw, come on... Hiccup shifts to get out of bed... then pauses... sensing that something is wrong.
{DIALOGUE}: He peels back the covers slowly.
{DIALOGUE}: What he sees startles, horrifies, and overwhelms him -- all at once.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 102.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON THE BARE FLOOR His booted foot touches down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Followed by a mechanical prosthetic in place of his second leg.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's an ingenious spring-loaded replacement, made of wood and iron.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Toothless lands by the bed and approaches calmly, sniffing the new leg.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He raises his eyes to meet Hiccup's, seemingly aware of what Hiccup is going through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup braces himself on the bedpost and tries to stand on it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He winces and stifles the pain...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay...okay... ... but STUMBLES with the first step.
{DIALOGUE}: Toothless catches Hiccup's fall with his head... and slowly lifts him up, stabilizing him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks bud.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup leans on him like a crutch.
{DIALOGUE}: They take a few steps together.
{DIALOGUE}: Their missing parts form a poetic silhouette as they make their way toward the door.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup pries it open (as he did in the opening scene), revealing a MONSTROUS NIGHTMARE flapping outside the door.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup YELPS and slams the door closed.
{DIALOGUE}: He turns to Toothless, alarmed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Toothless?
{DIALOGUE}: Stay here, bud.
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup pauses... and cracks the door open again.
{DIALOGUE}: He peeks outside, his eyes widening.
{DIALOGUE}: He allows to door to swing open, revealing... ... the Monstrous Nightmare, carrying Snotlout on its back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SNOTLOUT
{DIALOGUE}: Come on guys, get ready!
{DIALOGUE}: Hold on tight!
{DIALOGUE}: Here we go!
{DIALOGUE}: A class of newbie dragon riders follow him through frame on a variety of dragons, pulling back the curtain on an amazing vista in which:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Dragon" DeBlois/Sanders Final Draft (Rev.19) 02-13-2010 103.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vikings and dragons mill about by the dozen, basking on the rooftops, weaving along the plaza.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No one seems upset, there isn't a sword in sight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Under the framework of a MASSIVE BARN, a Nadder BLASTS fire onto a metal brace.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It steps back to let a Viking hammer it into shape.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nearby, a Gronkle lands, carrying a tree trunk in his mouth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shows a Viking what he's found.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Viking pats his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another Viking backs a Zippleback into a stall to check it for size.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hiccup takes a step outside, finding Stoick waiting for him on the step.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HICCUP
{DIALOGUE}: I knew it.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm dead.
{DIALOGUE}: Stoick laughs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK
{DIALOGUE}: No, but you gave it your best shot.
{DIALOGUE}: He puts his arm around Hiccup, steadying him.
{DIALOGUE}: He gestures to the transformed village.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: STOICK (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: So?
{DIALOGUE}: What do you think?
{DIALOGUE}: Hiccup just shrugs, amazed.
{DIALOGUE}: Below, the plaza, villagers take notice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VIKING #1
{DIALOGUE}: Hey look!
